So I'm here at the library at school, and the original intent was to study for Trig.  Stacey and I actually took initiative!  And it worked out for a while, but then we started to drift...I managed to look over my notes for a while, and I copied the notes from Thursday since I was out, and then I decided that that was all I would do.  Way to go Steph.  I'll look at it some more when I get home.  I mean, a couple hours of studying isn't too bad, right?  And I'm gonna study some more for Thursday, since that's when we have our first exam.  I'm not really stressing it though, since I already know the stuff and it's really all reviewing for me.  No biggie.  Anyways, I'm gonna go play a game now.  See ya!

So!  To pull my wisdom teeth out, it'll cost $778.  I mean it could be worse, but still.  Without my insurance it would have been $2050, so I really should be grateful, but that's still a lot of money that I have to pay.  My dad has decided that since it's my teeth, that I have to pay for it.  All of it.  Oy.  And to think that I didn't even want to have them pulled.  I'd rather sit and suffer.  Humph.  Anyways, that's all I have to report for now.  We'll see if I have anything to vent about later.  Grr....
So!  I am very confused...who is The One Armed Man??  I'd really like to know who's talking to me.  I'm not crazy, right?  Right?  Okay.  Hope to find out who you are mystery person!

So!  I've had a lovely weekend.  I got to spend time with lots of people and even went to see Shark Tale with Halis.  We went to Coco Walk to see it last night.  It was SOOO funny!  Everyone should go and see it pronto.  I knew that there would be adult humor in it, as usual, but there was an abundance this time.  Funny stuff.  And!  We even went exploring and found a new club that opened up.  It's called The Corner.  It has potential, although they need to promote more.  There wasn't very many people there.  Kinda slow to start, but there is definitely potential.  Anywhoo!  My fried chicken is calling my name.  Grub time!

So!  I've come to the conclusion that we all want what we can't have.  Like now for example.  I really want chocolate ice cream, but since I have to save my money for my car payment, I can't go and get some.  I mean, yes, I normally want chocolate ice cream, but since I can't have it at this very moment, I'm jonesing more than usual.  Grr.  But seriously.  I've even applied this to real life stuff too.  Take for instance, my friend John.  He works with me at GHETC and he's such a sweetheart.  He knows I have a bf and he also has a gf, but he still continuously flirts with me.  He jokingly told me that my bf better be careful, cuz he's gonna steal me away from him one day.  It's not gonna happen, obviously, but it's still applicable.  Interesting stuff, huh?  Coincidence?  Maybe, maybe not...

So! I had a really good first day of school. I was dreading going back though, but now I'm happy. It's a nice break from work, and I still get to be productive. I'm also happy that I get to see a lot of the crew during the day. It's nice to not have to sit by yourself for too long. I met a few interesting people as well. This girl in my Intro to Logic class, Catherine, can vibrate her eyes. Very scary. lol. Also, this girl, Megan, in my Intro to Environmental Science class transferred from FSU so we had lots to talk about. Interesting stuff. I like meeting new people. BUT! It's really great to be around people that I already know and love! It's reminiscent of Sunset. Happiness all around. Well! I'm gonna go now, but I hope everyone had a wonderful first day back, and for those of you who are still on campus:

                                           Just keep swimming, just keep swimming...

Have fun kiddies!

So!  I guess I'm under Code 7 now.  Yay!  I'm happy.  Took long enough!!  lmao.  Just kidding.  ((Not really, but you know how it is.))  And now, I'm off to bed, because I'm sleepy and I have to go to work tomorrow.  Bright and early!!  Grr...

I've decided that I really enjoy working.  It's difficult, time consuming, and physically exhausting, but at the end of the day, I have such a feeling of accomplishment.  As if I made a little difference in someone's life.  Ophelia is making much progress in just two days.  She hasn't thrown herself on the ground since she first got to Good Hope, and she's more attentive too.  I'm really proud of her.  I mean, don't get me wrong, she is still quite the handful.  Sometimes I just want to tell someone else to watch her and then go slam my head on the wall, but if she can put up with me, I can certainly deal with her.  It's just a matter of us both understanding that I don't work with her, she works with me.  I hope she continues progressing.  She has such potential.  I can see it.  Now we have to get her to see it for herself.  ::sigh::  Time for bed now.  More work in the morning.

Here are a few little messages that I thought were really nice.

*Enjoy life's sweet surprises.

*Enjoy life's simple pleasures.

*Make every moment count.

*Savor every moment.

*Inspire the life of a child.

Maybe if everyone thought in those terms and had a more positive outlook in life, things would get better for everyone.  Anything can happen, but it's important to remember that every grey cloud has a silver lining.  It's all about perpsective, and I think that we can all re-evaluate our priorities in order to achieve this state of contentment.  That is all.

Parentless house for the weekend + Sex crazed friends + Lotsa alcohol = Shitloads of fun.

Nuff said.

I just want to say that I love my job.  It's exhausting, but I still love it.  I mean, I get paid to play all day!  How great is that?!  Good times.

Today at work, we went to a Water Park.  It was uber fun.  All my girls are crazy though, but they are so cute.  However!  There was a slight complication.  There's this boy, Nick, who volunteers at the ranch and all the girls are absolutely IN LOVE with him.  So!  Everytime he came within ten feet of them, they went crazy and havoc ensued.  It was definitely an event and every five minutes, one of the girls would run off and Jess and I would have to run after them and drag them back.  Running after five little 11-year-old girls is a little tiring after a while.  And what made it worse is that Nick is always near me, cuz he kinda has a little crush on me.  

The part that complicates things is that the boy is 14!  And he knows I'm 19, but apparently, it doesn't matter to him cuz he constantly flirts with me.  I humor him sometimes, but I don't encourage him.  At first, I thought that I was overreacting, but on the bus ride back to Baptist Hospital, he asked to see my phone.  So I let him.  Then he changed my greeting  to "I LUV NICK."  Then he turned it off and said that he changed my greeting.  So I turned it back on and such and I saw it and I looked at him and kinda laughed and hit him and he smiled.  Oh the drama.  And now I have to worry about whether or not the girls in my group will hate me if they find out.  I know that sounds a little exaggerated, but do you people remember how we were in 6th grade?  How everything was life and death, black or white?  Yeah.  Here's hoping that they don't find out.

Anyways, I gotta go now.  I'm tired and I have to proof read James' essay.  Deuces.

So!  I had my first day of work and I feel accomplished.  Although, I just want to put it out there that three day old pee smells HEINOUS.  One of the less bright spots of the day.  However!  The rest of the day was cool.  It's a little tiring running around after little kids all day, but I managed to keep up pretty well.  I'm not that old...YET.  lol.  There was this little girl, Sarae, who is soooooo cute.  I just want to put her in my pocket and carry her around with me.  So cute.  And!  I already found one of the little kids annoying.  No one really likes her.  I don't remember her name though.  But Jess and I were talking about wanting to kick her in the face.  Our reasoning was, just because a person is sick doesn't give them the right to be a shit head to everyone.  And I really have a lot of patience with children, but I couldn't handle being around her for more than a half an hour.  Everyone was complaining, but I guess she can't help it.  She's just a little kid after all.  Maybe tomorrow I'll actually get to ride a horse...

So!  I'm being UBER productive today!  I'm very proud of myself.  I shampooed the carpets, cleaned the bathroom and am currently doing laundry.  I know, scary isn't it??  And the best part!  I decided to do it all on my own.  Yes, ladies and gentlemen, I was not told to do chores.  I am voluntarily doing them.  Stand back!  I think I'm growing up!  lol.
